<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1263,1522]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,300,1263,1289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Since the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck (1783: 87)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityPageNumber="87" authorityYear="1783" box="[526,961,1264,1290]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[526,708,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe tenuifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de" box="[717,961,1264,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5486" refString="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de. (1783) Encyclopedie Methodique, Botanique 1. Panckoucke, Paris, 748 pp." type="book" year="1783">Lamarck (1783: 87)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
already exists, this combination is not available for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berger" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Engl." box="[309,603,1303,1328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Chortolirion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolium">
<emphasis box="[309,603,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Chortolirion tenuifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new name commemorates Barend [Ben] Hermanus Groenewald (1905–1976), who described several new aloes from 
<collectingCountry box="[782,934,1341,1367]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">South Africa</collectingCountry>
during the 1930s and wrote the first book on the aloes of southern Africa that represented an up-to-date treatment for the subcontinent (
<bibRefCitation author="Groenewald, B. H." pageId="5" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5152" refString="Groenewald, B. H. (1941) Die Aalwyne van Suid-Afrika, Suidwes-Afrika, Portugees Oos-Afrika, Swaziland, Basoetoland en ' n Spesiale Ondersoek van die Klassifikasie, Chromosome en Areale van die Aloe maculatae. Nasionale Pers, Bloemfontein, 172 pp." type="book" year="1941">Groenewald 1941</bibRefCitation>
). Despite his valuable contributions towards our understanding of aloes in southern Africa, he did not receive the recognition he deserves and has never been commemorated in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1147,1201,1457,1482]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1201,1457,1482]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Anonymous &amp; Van Jaarsveld, E. J." box="[1217,1431,1457,1483]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="57 - 59" refId="ref4423" refString="Anonymous [Van Jaarsveld, E. J.]. (2010) Overlooked by history? Barend Hermanus Groenewald (Ben). Aloe 47: 57 - 59." type="journal article" year="2010">Anonymous 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Figueiredo, E. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[151,456,1496,1522]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="79 - 102" refId="ref4935" refString="Figueiredo, E. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2010) What's in a name: epithets in Aloe L. (Asphodelaceae) and what to call the next new species. Bradleya 28: 79 - 102." type="journal article" year="2010">Figueiredo &amp; Smith 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
